{"id":"datalinq-helper-recordstojs","name":null,"description":null,"code":"<div class=\"navbar\">\r\n  <div class=\"title\" id=\"function-title\"><a href=\"https://localhost:7277/datalinq/report/datalinq-guide@select-all-users@index\">DataLinq-Helper: RecordsToJs</a></div>\r\n  <div style=\"width: 30px;\"></div> \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"wrapper\">\r\n\r\n<button class=\"collapsible\">\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-label\">Basic Usage</span>\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-actions\">\r\n<span class=\"action-button\" onclick=\"openPopup(event, 'recordsToJs_basic')\">Code/Query</span>\r\n</span>\r\n</button>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n    @DLH.RecordsToJs(records: Model.Records, jsCallbackFuncName: \"basicUsage\")\r\n    <div id=\"basicUsage\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"description_recordsToJs_basic\" hidden>\r\nde:RecordsToJs(records: Model.Records, jsCallbackFuncName: \"basicUsage\") ermöglicht es, bereits im Modell vorhandene Daten (hier Model.Records) an eine JavaScript-Callback-Funktion zu übergeben. \r\nDie Funktion basicUsage wird aufgerufen und erhält diese Daten als Argument. \r\nIn diesem Beispiel wird aus den übergebenen Datensätzen der vollständige Name (Vorname + Nachname) jedes Benutzers zusammengefügt und im HTML-Element mit der ID basicUsage angezeigt.\r\n\r\nen:RecordsToJs(records: Model.Records, jsCallbackFuncName: \"basicUsage\") allows you to pass already present data (here Model.Records) to a JavaScript callback function. \r\nThe basicUsage function is invoked with the data as an argument. \r\nIn this example, the full name (first name + last name) of each user from the passed records is combined and displayed in the HTML element with the ID basicUsage.\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"csharp_recordsToJs_basic\" hidden><script type=\"text/plain\">\r\n@@DLH.RecordsToJs(records: Model.Records, jsCallbackFuncName: \"basicUsage\")\r\n<div id=\"basicUsage\"></div>\r\n\r\n    JS: (in script-tag)\r\n    window.basicUsage = function(data) \r\n    {\r\n        const fullNames = data.map(item => item[\"FirstName\"]+\" \"+item[\"LastName\"]).join(\", \");\r\n        document.getElementById(\"basicUsage\").textContent = fullNames;\r\n    }\r\n</script></div>\r\n<div id=\"sql_recordsToJs_basic\" hidden>SELECT * FROM Users</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<script>\r\n    window.basicUsage = function(data) \r\n    {\r\n        const fullNames = data.map(item => item[\"FirstName\"]+\" \"+item[\"LastName\"]).join(\", \");\r\n        document.getElementById(\"basicUsage\").textContent = fullNames;\r\n    }\r\n</script>","created":"2025-04-15T09:14:46","changed":"2025-05-09T07:05:28.667152Z","test_parameters":null,"included_js_libs":"legacy_chartjs"}